This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the problem of novel view synthesis, which is a common task in computer vision. Additionally, the paper also introduces a novel learning framework that combines Generative Query Network (GQN) and Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs), which are popular techniques in the field of computer vision. 

The paper also involves aspects of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as it proposes a new learning framework that combines two different generative models. 

The paper also involves aspects of Machine Learning (cs.LG) as it proposes a new learning framework that involves training a neural network to generate novel views. 

The paper may also belong to the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category as it deals with the problem of generating new views of a scene, which is a common task in computer graphics. 

Finally, the paper may also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as the ability to generate novel views of a scene is important for robots that need to navigate and interact with their environment.
